\par Videotaping was on the se
cond day.  Husband and wife left alone in the room with the camera, given a series of cards.  Interaction could be vivid: e.g. wife who wants to understand why the farm not doing well, husband just pulls his chair further away.  The couple were one unit, 
the children a second unit, and the whole family the third.  All coded by a standard system developed by Mavis Hetherington.
